CDC
September 8 at 3:54 PM ¬∑

Did you host or attend a Labor Day gathering? If you were in close contact with others, you may have been exposed to COVID-19.
Take steps to protect yourself and others:
- Wear a mask and stay at least 6 feet from others when you go out.
- Monitor your health. If you feel sick, stay home and call your healthcare provider.
- Write down who you were with and where you went during the weekend. Let them know if you get sick.
- Answer your phone if the health department calls. If you get a call from an unknown number, check your voicemail.

Learn more: https://bit.ly/2WajUx3.

post_text:
....and just like that our school year is over. Students are done and now our staff is done. We could not have imagined how this school year would end, and it is hard to imagine how next year will start. However, one thing is clear and that is that we will come together as a Minnehaha family and do whatever it takes to educate, support and love our students.

Please don‚Äôt believe all of the different memes, post and comments that do not come from a reliable source regarding our next school year. We know that school will look different next year, but we do not know exactly what that will look like.

When we have guidance from MDH and MDE, we will create a plan and share it with you. Please remember that the guidance from the state may not come for several weeks. Please be patient and remember that when we know something, you will know something.

Have a safe, healthy and most importantly a fun summer!! We hope to see you soon!! #MinnehahaStrong

post_text:
For parents that have asked about assignments "disappearing" after your child submits them on Google Classroom:

*Go to your child's Google Drive - Look under Folders - Click on Classroom
*This page will show you the different classrooms your child is a part of. Click on the classroom you need.
*You will be able to view the assignments that your child has turned in. You cannot edit them, but you can request access from the teacher if you want to edit them.

Please let us know if you have any questions.

post_text: We are very excited to have our very own Minnehaha Facebook page!! In an effort to simplify the info going out to our parents during these uncertain times, we have branched off from the Lake Superior School District's page. We will still share info that the district page posts, but we will eliminate posts specific to Two Harbors High School and William Kelley Schools. We hope this will make things easier for our families.
text: We are very excited to have our very own Minnehaha Facebook page!! In an effort to simplify the info going out to our parents during these uncertain times, we have branched off from the Lake Superior School District's page. We will still share info that the district page posts, but we will eliminate posts specific to Two Harbors High School and William Kelley Schools.
